Run it in this order.

1. Start infra
From project root:

cd C:\Users\oshin\Desktop\python1
docker compose up -d postgres redis qdrant
2. Install backend deps

cd C:\Users\oshin\Desktop\python1\backend
..\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pip install -r requirements.txt
3. Apply database migrations

..\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m alembic upgrade head
4. Start backend API
Open one terminal:

cd C:\Users\oshin\Desktop\python1\backend
..\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
Backend will run at:

http://127.0.0.1:8000
5. Start Celery worker
Open a second terminal:

cd C:\Users\oshin\Desktop\python1\backend
..\.venv\Scripts\celery.exe -A app.celery_app.celery_app worker --loglevel=info --pool=solo
--pool=solo is important on Windows.

6. Start frontend
Open a third terminal:

cd C:\Users\oshin\Desktop\python1\frontend
npm install
npm run dev
Frontend will run at:

http://127.0.0.1:5173
7. Ollama
Your backend uses qwen3:4b, so make sure Ollama is installed and the model is available:

ollama pull qwen3:4b
ollama serve
Usually Ollama already runs in the background after installation.

Then open:

http://127.0.0.1:5173
Register a user, log in, upload PDF/TXT docs, wait for indexing, then use chat/search.